OL,5, Higher-education providers in England  
OL,6, have an "unhealthy dependency" on      
OL,7, international students, to compensate  
OL,8, for frozen tuition fees and increased  
OL,9, costs, a Lords committee report warns. 
OL,11,FNeither the government nor the         
OL,12,Fregulator, the Office for Students, is 
OL,13,Ftackling the "looming crisis", the     
OL,14,FIndustry and Regulators Committee says.
OL,16,FThe OfS lacks independence and is not  
OL,17,Ftrusted by providers, the report says. 
OL,19,FBut the OfS said it had taken steps to 
OL,20,Faddress many of the issues raised.     
